___Static

 8th July 2023 at 12:17pm
static

This tiddler usually appears at the top of the static page representing the content of the main TiddlyWiki notebook with all the tiddlers together in one place in an infinite list. This is a single HTML file that can be downloaded (Ctrl-S) for offline reading, the sources can be viewed using Ctrl-U, and a quick search can be performed using Crtl-F. It does not contain all of the functionality of the main TiddlyWiki and is intended to be viewable in web browsers that have JavaScript disabled.

CSS handling

 2nd July 2023 at 11:48pm
Examples

The original CSS from KaTeX includes a number of font definitions in this format :

@font-face {
  font-family: 'KaTeX_AMS';
  src: url(fonts/KaTeX_AMS-Regular.woff2) format('woff2'), url(fonts/KaTeX_AMS-Regular.woff) format('woff'), url(fonts/KaTeX_AMS-Regular.ttf) format('truetype');
  font-weight: normal;
  font-style: normal;
}

These definitions are currently removed manually from $:/plugins/orange/katex-tw5/katex.min.css so that they can be redefined as data URIs using TiddlyWiki's macro notation in $:/plugins/orange/katex-tw5/styles

@font-face {
	font-family: KaTeX_AMS;
	src: url(<<datauri '$:/plugins/orange/katex-tw5/fonts/KaTeX_AMS-Regular.woff2'>>) format('woff2');
	font-weight: 400;
	font-style: normal;
}

Note that the plugin currently only embeds the WOFF2 format fonts, which seems to be sufficient for most browsers.

  • Sind v1,…,vrv_1,\ldots,v_rv1​,…,vr​ linear unabhängig, so gibt es mindestens eine lineare Abbildung F ⁣:V→WF\colon V\to WF:V→W mit F(vi)=wiF(v_i)=w_iF(vi​)=wi​ für i=1,…,r.i=1,\ldots,r.i=1,…,r.
  • Ist (v1,…,vr)(v_1,\ldots,v_r)(v1​,…,vr​) eine Basis, so gibt es genau ein solches FFF und es hat folgende Eigenschaften:

HelloThere

 11th July 2023 at 12:56pm

Welcome to my TiddlyWiki (TW) dedicated to the KaTeX TW5 Plugin for mathematical typesetting, based on Khan Academy's KaTeX. It is fully self-contained and does not need an Internet connection to work.

I'm not the author of the plugin, I just took what was already done and updated the KaTeX files. All credit goes to the original authors, and the works follow their licenses. Some sources :

  • https://tiddlywiki.com/plugins/tiddlywiki/katex
  • https://katex.org
  • https://kookma-katex.tiddlyhost.com

The plugin adds 0.8 MB to the TW 5.3.0 empty file size (2.3 MB), for a total of 3.1 MB. KaTeX fonts in the WOFF2 format were used, which occupy 254 kB, instead of the 296 kB of the WOFF format, representing a reduction of approximately 15%.

In addition, I have also included the Regular Latin Open Sans font (18 kB) in the plugin. The Fonts tiddler has a list of available fonts, which can be used normally anywhere in TW. They can even be used as the Notebook's default font, see Font family and Code font family in the ControlPanel of this TW. Other fonts can be easily added using the Node.js version of TW, just download the WOFF2 file, place it in the plugin's fonts directory, and add an entry in styles.tid.

How to upgrade

 1st July 2023 at 10:29pm

The following steps use the TiddlyWiki on Node.js (TWN) :

  • Clone the sources from TiddlyWiki github with git clone --depth 1 --branch v5.3.0 https://github.com/Jermolene/TiddlyWiki5.git [1]
  • Download the latest KaTeX release from https://github.com/KaTeX/KaTeX/releases [2]
  • One way to update is by creating a new empty TW using TWN, and copying the files from [1] and [2] to the plugins directory
  • Manually edit the katex.min.css file and remove the lines with "@font-face{...}"
  • In the fonts directory, only ".woff2" files are used, and the styles.tid and tiddlywiki.files files need to be changed to accommodate the WOFF2 format.
  • Update the version inside the plugin.info file
  • Check all the other files one by one to see if they are working and up to date
  • To check using the browser, go into the wiki directory and start the server with TIDDLYWIKI_PLUGIN_PATH=./plugins tiddlywiki --listen
  • In the case of plugin files, it is necessary to edit the file directly, on the file system, using an external editor. However, the changes are not automatically updated in the browser. It is necessary to restart the server to see the changes
  • Once everything is verified and working, simply use the cloud button and select "Save snapshot for offline use" to generate a tiddlywiki.html file containing the wiki and plugin

KaTeX Plugin Macro

 2nd July 2023 at 11:46pm
Examples

There are two methods to define KaTeX macros

  1. Using a tiddler tagged with $:/tags/AboveStory
  2. Using the KaTeX plugin config tab $:/plugins/orange/katex-tw5/config

Use Above Story Tag

  • Create a new tiddler
  • Tag it with $:/tags/AboveStory
  • add your macro definition as below
  • see for example Test Macros Defined Globally
    • the body have a $$...$$ block
    • each macro is defined using \gdef in its own line

Use the Config Tab of KaTeX Plugin

  • Goto $:/plugins/orange/katex-tw5/config
  • Open the Config tab
  • Method i: use the custom macro editor
    • add a macro name like \foo
    • add the commands like \mathbb{Z}
    • click add buton
  • Method ii: use the import box
    • enter your macro one by one in the import box
    • as an example \def\myfrac#1#2{\frac{#1}{#2}}
    • enter all other macro definition
    • review the macros enetered under Preview
    • click import to add all macros at once
Remarks
in KaTeX you can ignore arguments in header e.g. instead of \def\foo#1, you can have \def\foo. KaTeX is smart to recognize the input arguments
the recomendation is to give the argument in macro definition
